CO-OPERATIVE Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Des van Rooyen says President Jacob Zuma is the hero of the masses.Van Rooyen says when the real history is told about Zuma, he will be remembered for "bringing hope to millions of South Africa's citizens".He was praising Zuma at the opening of the Traditional Leaders Indaba at Birchwood Hotel in Ekurhuleni this morning.Van Rooyen said Zuma should be celebrated as the leader whose trademark has been the struggle for the voiceless.He said the sacrifices that were made by Zuma have guided his own actions to ensure that services delivery is improved for the poorest of the poor.Van Rooyen says Zuma is the hero of the voiceless citizens who do not have access to Twitter and Facebook."We know very well that he is not a friend to monopoly capital, we know very well that he is shaking a lot of things. His leadership has changed the lives of the poorest of the poor." Van Rooyen said.This comments come after Zuma survived another motion of no confidence tabled against him at a meeting of the ANC's national executive committee (NEC) in Pretoria at the weekend.It also follows the revelations on Sunday of emails linked to the controversial Gupta family. The emails show that the Guptas picked up the tab for Van Rooyen's visit to Dubai in 2015.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/zuma-a-hero-of-the-masses-des-van-rooyen-20170529